days, learning and sharing in an open-space format (you can find the\nsession plans here: "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Sunday"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/tacker/30109096515/in/album-72157671333742283/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Monday"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/tacker/29481516243/in/album-72157671333742283/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"). Most of the attendees were\neither scrum masters, product owners or consultants that teach people how to\nfill this roles. Tech people were rather underrepresented, which actually is a\ngood thing: I find getting to know other perspectives to be very helpful in your\nday to day work. Especially we as developers are notoriously sticking to \"our\npeople\" ‚Ä¶ "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"if we leave our workplace at all"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#agile-as-a-starter-for-organizational-transformation","ariaLabel":"agile as a starter for organizational transformation permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Agile"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" as a starter for organizational transformation?"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"agile-as-a-starter-for-organizational-transformation","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Now for the part that kept me busy during these two days; a lot of the sessions\ndealt with variants of this question:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"How can my team and I work in an agile fashion, while the rest of my\norganisation is not agile?"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The experience of many attendees is, that many companies are running their agile\nprojects mainly for two reasons that are driven by management"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"increase the output of IT projects,"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"make more profit."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ol","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/96RObOuTT5Nh1EvFZjj3m/ef4601cab2f639028e0e8d93582da853/1_nwNT2FhSgjq9FHogVI87dw.jpeg?w=1000&h=1414","alt":"1*nwNT2FhSgjq9FHogVI87dw"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Oftentimes it seems to be a decision based on hearsay ("},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\"We've heard about this\nnew thing, that everyone else does, so lets do it, too!\""}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://geek-and-poke.com/geekandpoke/2016/4/26/finally-agile","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"). Improving\nproduct quality and customer satisfactions rarely are the driving factors nor is\nimproving the working conditions for employees."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The missing understanding of the core values behind the agile movement and the\ndisposition as experiments obviously leads to a lot of friction and conflicts\nbetween the agile teams and the rest of the company and puts these teams under\nextra pressure. Now they are not only quested with the success of the project\nusing a new way to work with which they have no experience but with leading the\nimplementing agile within the whole organization."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"These endeavors are bound to fail and the failure will be attributed to\nshortcomings of the agile methodology and not to the inability of classical,\nhierarchical structures to support agile teams at all."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"To ask for advice how to make these agile teams or projects \"work\" in these\ncircumstances is one option, but that does not fix the root cause of the\nproblem: the organization itself."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Network organizations are an enabler for agility, self-organisation and creates\na focus on delivering customer value. These are environments in which agile\nteams can thrive and will be successful."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"So I set out and collected problems agile teams face in order to show, that\nthere are indeed solutions to these problem, but they usually are not that\nobvious and need to be applied at a different level in order to become\neffective."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/4ihaprxZOPyOLQ3hr8W8GO/82ec38f76180ccd043a749c9e85c594c/1_woxzYPiopsfBm4nwPIOT5Q.jpeg?w=1200&h=1520","alt":"1*woxzYPiopsfBm4nwPIOT5Q"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You can find the long list "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"here"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/tacker/29994987272/in/album-72157671333742283/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", and I'm sure it can easily be extended\neven further. After I had this material, I used the evening in the hotel to\ncompile our tools and measures of choice we use to fix these problems. I wanted\nto show, that there is a solution to every single problem. It might not be\nsimple, but we've done it in the past. "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This flipchart"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/tacker/29481083554/in/album-72157671333742283/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" gives you an\nidea. \"Unfortunately\" we had a very lively discussion, so the note-taking-part\non my side came a little short but I was able to show a fix for every problem,\nand I might go into some of them in the comments, if you are interested."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#agile-is-a-seed-and-seeds-need-a-soil","ariaLabel":"agile is a seed and seeds need a soil permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Agile"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" is a seed, and seeds need a soil"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"agile-is-a-seed-and-seeds-need-a-soil","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"My takeaway from the conference is that agile practitioners need to identify the\nroot causes for the problems and stop trying to handle the symptoms."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You can't just plant an agile project into your organization without providing\nthe grounds for it to grow roots."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"type":"root","data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Agile as a starter for organizational transformation?","subtitle":null,"noheadline":null,"date":"2016-10-03T18:00:00.000Z","abstract":"Impressions from the Agile Cologne XXL 2016","lang":null},"headings":[{"id":"agile-as-a-starter-for-organizational-transformation","depth":2,"value":"Agile as a starter for organizational transformation?"},{"id":"agile-is-a-seed-and-seeds-need-a-soil","depth":2,"value":"Agile is a seed, and seeds need a soil"}]}},"Footer":{"id":"cfe5b9e2-511c-5615-992a-dab82e1f8ed7","name":"Footer","relativeDirectory":"","relativePath":"Footer.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Nordic Semiconductor"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://nordicsemi.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."},{"children":[],"tagName":"br","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nMentor. Speaker. Conference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1